  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels fall below required levels for the majority of factors. Decision record reflects a conditional acceptance pending resolution of outstanding gaps. A key reference cited in the numerical verification rationale (Garon & Farinas, 2004) is identified by DOI but the corresponding node is not declared in this package.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-credibility",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis",
